om, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":11,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":36,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Thomas Culpeper of Bayhall was born in 1279, in Tonbridge, Kent, England, United Kingdom as the son of Thomas Colpeper and Margery Bayhall. He had at least 2 sons with Margery Bayhall. He died in 1321, in Winchelsea, Sussex, England, at the age of 42, and was buried in Winchelsea, Sussex, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1279–1321":"1279–1321","1264–Male":"1264–Surnud","1271–1318":"1271–1318","–1307":"–1307","1305–1376":"1305–1376","1307–Male":"1307–Surnud","1240–1311":"1240–1311","1264":"1264","1240":"1240","1271":"1271","Abt 1305":"umbes 1305","1290":"1290","1305":"1305","1315":"1315","about 1307":"umbes 1307","1279":"1279","1311":"1311","1321":"1321","1376":"1376","1307":"1307","after 1311":"pärast 1311","1318":"1318","1317":"1317","Winchelsea, Sussex, England":"Winchelsea, Sussex, England","England":"England","Brenchley, Kent, England":"Brenchley, Kent, England","Pembury, Kent, England":"Pembury, Kent, England","Winchelsea, Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Winchelsea, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tonbridge, Kent, England":"Tonbridge, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1279–1321":"1279–1321","1264–Male":"1264–Kuollut","1271–1318":"1271–1318","–1307":"–1307","1305–1376":"1305–1376","1307–Male":"1307–Kuollut","1240–